summary:
The Security Council,

Recalling its previous resolutions and presidential statements on Sudan and South Sudan,

Welcoming progress on the Joint Border Verification and Monitoring Mechanism (JBVMM),

Stressing the need for Sudan and South Sudan to implement JBVMM,

Commending assistance from the African Union High-level Implementation Panel (AUHIP) and UNISFA,

Noting the Secretary-General's report (S/2018/778),

Recognizing the threat to international peace and security,

1. Extends UNISFA's mandate modification until 15 October 2019, as final extension unless parties take specific measures;
2. Decides to decrease UNISFA's troop ceiling by 557 troops as of 15 October 2019 unless mandate modification is extended;

Parties must demonstrate progress on border demarcation by:

1. Ensuring UNISFA patrols have freedom of movement;
2. Withdrawing troops from Abu Qussa/Wunkur;
3. Convening JPSM sessions;
4. Withdrawing from the Safe Demilitarized Border Zone (SDBZ);
5. Opening border crossing corridors;
6. Holding Joint Border Commission and Joint Demarcation Committee meetings;
7. Deploying national monitors;

4. Encourages AUHIP to engage with parties to resolve border disputes;

5. Intends to request the Secretary-General to update on reconfiguration of UNISFA mandate;

6. Requests the Secretary-General to report on progress by 15 September 2019;

7. Remains seized of this matter.
